        "level": 1
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "framework — the methodology"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-lead-2": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-lead-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "@codecaine-ai/docs-framework-skill",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the documentation methodology: the how-to-run-docs-in-a-project layer. It contains guidance and reusable authoring material, not runtime code."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-owns-heading-3": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-owns-heading-3",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "What it owns"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-owns-4": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-owns-4",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "At "
        },
        {
          "insert": "packages/framework/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", it owns the manual—architecture reference, standards, hierarchy conventions, and setup guide—plus document templates and the skill definition that host repositories symlink into their agent tooling."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-package-heading-5": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-package-heading-5",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Why it is a package at all"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-package-6": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-package-6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The honest reason is distribution convenience. Being a workspace package lets a host repository resolve, version, and symlink the methodology like any other dependency; the packaging is not an architectural layer."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-dependencies-heading-7": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-dependencies-heading-7",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Dependencies"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-dependencies-8": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-dependencies-8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "None. The package has zero dependencies and imports nothing. Nothing depends on it at runtime, and it does not ship in the server, viewer, or CLI. A running docs installation behaves identically whether the package is present or absent."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-alone-heading-9": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-alone-heading-9",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Using it alone"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-alone-10": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-alone-10",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A repository can adopt the manual, templates, and skill without running any of the software. In that mode, it uses only the documentation method."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-70-framework-boundary-11": {
      "id": "b-70-framework-boundary-11",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "kind": "Boundary under review",
        "title": "This may not need to be a package",
        "tone": "info"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Framework-as-package is itself under review. It may not need to remain a workspace package at all; the same material could live as plain repository content or use its own distribution channel."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    }
  }
